<paragraph id="41FBEAEA893623E2A556307B7FA2C69E" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">The Republic of Korea</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1F33A2B199FAC9F972A0E1691AF6885A" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="B1C22F5969B88502D4049C05AD6CBFF5" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remark.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E9FC89D55D7AA5DB39FF5F6475285AED" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
<taxonomicName id="98E8A9038D7771ECB80D67DD244524B7" authorityName="J. S. Kim &amp; Y. W. Lim" authorityYear="2022" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis clavicystidiata" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="clavicystidiata">
<emphasis id="A7213699CA9757C888953DAC9347180D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis clavicystidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="65F391A1487A99B106DE595FD72D1769" genus="G." lsidName="G. omphalodes" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="omphalodes">
<emphasis id="064F6BBA0CFD4B0935C20C24F044F964" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">G. omphalodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="17B4B06E80385DBF869C1AE6C2BA551C" genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. menehune" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="menehune">
<emphasis id="AF0DD05030BAC42742FC4A91E469C96B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. menehune</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="2911854D5E669251BD9A7CFDADF83481" authorityName="J. S. Kim &amp; Y. W. Lim" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Kim &amp; Cho &amp; Park &amp; Park &amp; Kim &amp; Kim &amp; Lim" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis omphalodes" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="omphalodes">
<emphasis id="0AECA35B93923C61AA62C2876DEC8A00" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis omphalodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in their larger pileus (2-30 mm), a darker colored stipe, smaller basidiospores (5-6 
<normalizedToken id="E12884898556D886D2FAC4C6A2A17D1D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.5-3 
<normalizedToken id="A5C2C283E6421EBF270E5BDCBCC1D604" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
), and thinner hyphae in the pileipellis (5-8 
<normalizedToken id="CE1B55A67A475F1F130E7A468C143D7D" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
wide). 
<taxonomicName id="4F0736524121829A18A46E8D33F8A726" authorityName="R.H.Petersen" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Desjardin, Halling &amp; Hemmes" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis menehune" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="menehune">
<emphasis id="F5D563CA7E5B19A8158DE40EA12D7FAE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis menehune</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="7A3966E713CAD50633B5DCA588CEE74D" genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. clavicystidiata" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="clavicystidiata">
<emphasis id="A761D45F0BA26D9FC9FBDE2C1779A649" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. clavicystidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its larger pileus (8-30 mm), buff lamellae, longer stipe (15-60 mm), longer basidiospores (7.5-9.5 
<normalizedToken id="750F3655D2C36ABD6ADF82840A7A1C5D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.5-4.2 
<normalizedToken id="4B0BBF3A5D1803C885FD8F3EA8897BCE" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, Q = 2.2), and longer caulocystidia (16-67 
<normalizedToken id="44A186E7B2663A2A5687EBCFE092C520" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-5 
<normalizedToken id="0AD9B95A2EB2612113DC8F82F04EC2B8" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="AD243C9D074BB98FB688C46DE6CA7A86" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" author="Desjardin, DE" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" pagination="166 - 176" refId="B10" refString="Desjardin, DE, Halling, RE, Hemmes, DE, 1999. Agaricales of the Hawaiian Islands. 5. The genera Rhodocollybia and Gymnopus. Mycologia 91 (1): 166 - 176, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" title="Agaricales of the Hawaiian Islands. 5. The genera Rhodocollybia and Gymnopus." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/3761206" volume="91" year="1999">Desjardin et al. 1999</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="BE5CAB0D60FE7A9FC91D7C2FD7FC2AD2" genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. clavicystidiata" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="clavicystidiata">
<emphasis id="0987EBFCC0EA146C63A33F47E7921ACC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. clavicystidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is phylogenetically close to 
<taxonomicName id="DB6E1703673DE7E3C7F042A5D0BC1D60" genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. pseudomphalodes" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="pseudomphalodes">
<emphasis id="AD9BDD283D165E5100D9533029696AE0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. pseudomphalodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="0281121E3765B993DA6F1B12CE8CDAB3" authorityName="J. S. Kim &amp; Y. W. Lim" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Kim &amp; Cho &amp; Park &amp; Park &amp; Kim &amp; Kim &amp; Lim" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Collybiopsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Collybiopsis pseudomphalodes" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="pseudomphalodes">
<emphasis id="7D8182DCAACCB61AF30280A3057E110C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Collybiopsis pseudomphalodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has relatively few references for comparison, but differences can be found in the lengths of the stipe (3-4 mm) and cheilocystidia (40 
<normalizedToken id="6DF236DA999B3A67B4B58D93C3928C32" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3 
<normalizedToken id="A3C840D10CFF488840FAE34160767115" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) when compared with 
<taxonomicName id="29DB6B63A11956492981832A7FCE3066" genus="Co." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Co. clavicystidiata" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="clavicystidiata">
<emphasis id="BC32A187175B7D4AFDBF6F307A0CD8F4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Co. clavicystidiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="CF2CA1C550C290BC4E584684DE5A9730" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4115784" author="Dennis, R" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the British Mycological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B8" refString="Dennis, R, 1961. Fungi venezuelani: IV. Agaricales. Kew Bulletin 15(1): 67-156[+ii]. https://doi.org/10.2307/4115784" title="Fungi venezuelani: IV. Agaricales. Kew Bulletin 15 (1): 67 - 156 [+ ii]." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4115784" year="1961">Dennis 1961</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
